nFromWeb?topicID=22641.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Family  VS  EQ</span><hr size=1> People who tell you to stop playing EQ are like women who lead their crusade like organizations. Always trying to opress their views on you. Who are you to tell me it's ruining my life? Beleive it or not some people might not actually want to be a sucessful athlete/business man etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udizzykid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dizzy Kid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 2:34:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22641.topic&index=36>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://dizzykid.homestead.com/files/eyes01.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Family  VS  EQ</span><hr size=1> Shehab - When I turned 18, I promptly moved to AZ to live with my grandmother. She was having some probs and I helped her out. Well, I'm in a new city and don't know *anyone*. So I'm playing EQ and I join a guild where we raid all the time. Turned out there was a bunch of them from my area. So we hooked up and we hang out now. =p We're all heavy gamers for the most part and all is cool.<br>
<br>
The connections I've made through EQ have gotten me a nice job with a simple phone call. Other connections have gotten me to help start up a communications network. =) I can't regret playing EQ ever and neither can anyone else who cares about me either.<br>
<br>
--DK-- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uilse3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ilse3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/02 3:41:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22641.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ravden.</span><hr size=1> The problem is--and you will find this is true with any addiction, virtual or otherwise--most people don't recognize they have a problem at the time they have the problem.  For a lot of people, it's only when looking back that they realize the problems inherint with whatever it was they were doing.  It's a little easier with drugs and alcohol as these things have been around for a long time; however, online gaming is still in its relative infancy.  I suspect it will only grow as a problem.  <br>
<br>
I don't regard casual playing as a problem, either.  This is directed at the 6-8+ hours a day people, and there are a _ton_ of them, however reticent they may be to admit it.<br>
<br>
The people who are trying to get you to stop may not be doing so out of some kind of pretentious crusade, but simply because they have been at it longer and it's easier to see when you look in reverse.  <br>
<br>
I was an online gaming addict quite a while before the Internet was a household word, and I suspect long before most people reading this now could even conceive of an online game, starting with mock MUSH's on IRC, and then to the first of the D&amp;D based text MUDs.  12 years later I am playing EQ, and by looking back on some of those years, am filled with an intense sadness and regret, that those of you playing EQ as a significant portion of your daily life will not experience until years from now.  <br>
<br>
In short, while I am sure you disagree now, you will understand some day, unless you take the necessary steps right now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion>Main Lounge</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
